The paper deals with spatio-temporal receptive fields, which are commonly used in computer vision and image processing. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of Gaussian receptive fields and first-order integrators, which are common in neural networks and machine learning, suggesting that cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are also likely sub-categories. The paper also presents a theoretical analysis of the receptive fields, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.IT (Information Theory).
